ins, Paul Fix, Alan Hale Jr, Lowell Gilmore, Richard Davalos, James Arness, John Qualen, Lyle Bettger, Tab Hunter, Peter Whitney, David Farrar, Lana Turner, Alma Beltran, John Doucette, Wilton Graff, Luis Van Rooten, Abdullah Abbas, Joe Brooks, Roger Cr A two hour plod, but at least it has one of the worst shark attacks scenes I've experienced so far (cinematic ally speaking, of course). Ehrlich says that if they catch the Ergenstrasse they can read the truth in his log. 1955; 1 hr 57 mins Drama NR Watchlist. For some critics, the presence of its stars introduced a note of unreality in an otherwise fairly valid portrait of one man’s allegiance to his country. or. As the Second World War breaks out, German freighter captain Karl Ehrlich is about to leave Sydney, Australia with his vessel, the Ergenstrasse. Apartment & Condo Building in Orange Beach, Alabama. When Ehrlich's fiercely Nazi chief officer Kirchner commits an atrocity, the British pursuit becomes deadly. 5. Opposed to the Nazis and at war with the British, Ehrlich and his crew are hunted by both sides. Warner Bros bought the film rights to the novel, which was published in 1948,[5] and John Wayne was announced for the lead in June 1951, with Bolton Mallory reported to be working on the script. The Sea Chase is yet another ’50s film seemingly intent on fine tuning public attitudes toward foreign policy. Napier flies to England as the Ergenstrasse, resupplied with coal and lifeboats, departs for Germany. Privileged college student Andy Shaeffer is a mama's boy who flunks out of school and is drafted by the army where he becomes a real man, to the astonishment of everyone. A C-47 transport plane, named the Corsair, makes a forced landing in the frozen wastes of Quebec, and the plane's pilot, Captain Dooley, must keep his men alive in deadly conditions while waiting for rescue. Although both the Caribbean Sea and the coastline of Mexico were considered as shooting locations, some parts of the film were shot in